    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 large eggs</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1/4 cup onion, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup bell pepper, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup cooked and shredded chicken (optional)</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>Black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>2 large tortillas or roti</li>
            <li>Sauce or chutney of your choice for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, beat the eggs and season with salt and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a skillet over medium heat.</li>
            <li>Add sliced onions and bell peppers to the skillet. Saut√© until they are softened.</li>
            <li>If using chicken, add the cooked and shredded chicken to the skillet and mix with the vegetables.</li>
            <li>Push the vegetables and chicken to one side of the skillet and add the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to the empty side.</li>
            <li>Pour the beaten eggs into the empty side of the skillet. Allow them to set for a few seconds, then scramble them until fully cooked.</li>
            <li>Mix the scrambled eggs with the vegetables and chicken in the skillet. Season with additional salt and black pepper if needed.</li>
            <li>Warm the tortillas or roti in the skillet or microwave.</li>
            <li>Place the egg and vegetable mixture in the center of each tortilla or roti. Roll them up tightly into a wrap.</li>
            <li>Serve the Egg Rolls hot with your favorite sauce or chutney.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious and filling Egg Rolls!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

